  <p>Reducing dependency size often improves performance more than optimising load behaviour.</p>

  <h3>Fallback and Failure Strategies</h3>

  <p>External services (APIs, analytics, ads, widgets) can sometimes fail or be slow. Your website should remain functional and usable even when these services are unavailable.</p>

  <p>Recommended strategies include:</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Progressive Enhancement</strong> – Build the core experience first, then enhance with additional features</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Graceful Degradation</strong> – Features degrade smoothly without breaking the main functionality</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Fallback UI Components</strong> – Display placeholder content if the service fails</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item"><strong>Error Handling for API Calls</strong> – Catch and handle errors to prevent crashes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Example: Safe API Fetch with Fallback</h3>

  <pre class="vf-code-example__pre"><code>// URL of the external API
const api = 'https://example.com/data';

// Fetch data from the API
fetch(api)
  .then(response => {
    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error('API request failed');
    }
    return response.json();
  })
  .then(data => {
    // Render the data on the page
    renderData(data);
  })
  .catch(error => {
    // Log the error for debugging
    console.error('API fetch error:', error);
    // Show fallback UI to the user
    showFallbackMessage('Data is currently unavailable. Please try again later.');
  });

// Example rendering functions
function renderData(data) {
  const container = document.getElementById('data-container');
  container.textContent = JSON.stringify(data, null, 2);
}

function showFallbackMessage(message) {
  const container = document.getElementById('data-container');
  container.textContent = message;
}</code></pre>

  <h3>CDN and Distribution</h3>

  <p>Third-party libraries can also benefit from global content delivery networks. CDNs reduce latency by serving resources from servers closer to users.</p>

  <p>However, developers should still ensure that CDN usage does not introduce unnecessary dependencies or tracking scripts.</p>

  {# ── Do / Don't ── #}
  <h2 id="dos-dont" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400 vf-search-client-side--no-index">Do / Don't</h2>

  <h3>Do</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Audit dependencies regularly</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Load scripts asynchronously</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Lazy load widgets and embeds</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Self-host critical libraries when possible</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Test dependency performance on slow networks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Don't</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Add dependencies without evaluating impact</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Allow third-party scripts to block rendering</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Rely heavily on large frameworks for simple tasks</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ignore external service failure scenarios</li>
  </ul>

  {# ── Checklist ── #}
  <h2 id="checklist" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Checklist</h2>

  <p>Before adding a new dependency:</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Confirm the dependency is necessary</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Check file size and performance impact</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Review maintenance activity</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Evaluate security vulnerabilities</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Ensure asynchronous loading</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Implement fallback behaviour</li>
  </ul>

  {# ── Metrics and Tools ── #}
  <h2 id="metrics" class="vf-u-margin--0 vf-u-padding__top--400">Metrics and Tools</h2>

  <p>Developers should measure the performance impact of third-party scripts.</p>

  <h3>Important metrics</h3>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Total number of third-party requests</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Total third-party transfer size</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">CPU time used by third-party scripts</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Main-thread blocking time</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Impact on Core Web Vitals</li>
  </ul>

